OL,6,FMr Cryan added that the organ at St
OL,7,FMary Redcliffe was famous around the
OL,8,Fworld.
OL,10,F"Handel played it and Howells. We have
OL,11,Fa history of big musical players using
OL,12,Four organ to structure how music can
OL,13,Fsound in the Church. So why not think
OL,14,Fof it in different ways?"
OL,16,FAccording to the church's records, the
OL,17,Ffamous composer Handel was friends
OL,18,Fwith the Vicar of St Mary Redcliffe,
OL,19,FThomas Broughton, in the 1700s.
